text:
Cal Fire reported another day of progress in battling the Zogg Fire near Redding that killed four people after breaking out Sunday. 

It grew by only 150 acres during the day, bring the total burned land to 56,168 acres, and it now is 56% contained. https://t.co/6syeAJsCOK
